unittitle_ssm: New York University School of Commerce, Accounts and Finance publicity scrapbook
abstract_ssm: The New York University School of Commerce, Accounts and Finance was established in 1900 to provide professional training for students pursuing a career in business. In 1988, the school was renamed the Leonard N. Stern School of Business. The collection contains a scrapbook with printed ephemera produced by the NYU School of Commerce, Accounts and Finance. The materials within the scrapbook promote the various programs and courses offered by the school. Materials date from 1936 to 1938.
